neighborhood_overview: Compton is a residential community of working-class families that offers an authentic and dynamic cultural experience with nearly 100,000 residents. Centrally located just south of the Los Angeles Metropolitan area downtown, the city enables visitors to drive to many of Los Angeles‚Äô best attractions in just 30 minutes. Technically known as the ‚ÄúHub City‚Äù because of its unique position in almost the exact geographical center of Los Angeles County, Compton is very close to both Hollywood and Disneyland, and boasts an aeronautical museum that is popular locally as a place to instill interest in pilot careers for younger museum goers.  Compton is also known for being the birthplace of countless star athletes such as Serena and Venus Williams, as well as a number of Hollywood favorites like Anthony Anderson, Kevin Costner, and even Ava DuVernay.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is called Sunset Mesa and is right at the very start of Malibu. This offers east access to Santa Monica [ about 10 to 30 minutes - depending on traffic!] and about 10 minutes to Malibu Pier and the Malibu Shopping are. This area is a real gem and relatively undiscovered. Practically a gated community with one road in and out with access to the PCH [ Pacific Coast Highway]. Wide streets for easy parking, no unsightly over head wires, great views to the ocean. Very safe for walking day and night and great for young kids. We love the fact that we can walk down the street to the beach in front of the Getty Villa.
We have access cards for the Getty - free entry and you don't have to book ! The Santa Monica mountains abut the back of this small neighborhood and are hikes into the Santa Monica Mountains and Malibu State Park. This is a very tranquil and relaxing neighborhood.

Full high-end sports club/gym located a few blocks away and guests may have access

Located next to Mar Vista, between Culver City and Venice, Palms is the oldest neighborhood annexed to Los Angeles, founded in 1886 by three entrepreneurs who saw potential in a mostly flat and fertile parcel of land. These founders subdivided the land for sale to individual families, then transplanted 5,000 palm trees to line the streets. The individual plots for sale were designed to be large enough to host a home as well as a small yard for family gardening in order to take advantage of the fertile soil.
The advertisements to Westward bound settlers proclaimed: ‚ÄúNo cold winters. No hot summers. No saloons at The Palms.‚Äù
Walkable neighborhood, lots of trees, pleasant breezy.
Great place for tourists, students or business people, whether traveling alone or as couple/friends.

I have enjoyed traveling and experiencing the local culture through the warm welcoming and kindness of AirBnB hosts. I intend to do the same for my guests by providing them with a clean safe, peaceful, and very comfortable place.
I celebrate and appreciate the commonalities of our diversity - everyone is welcome!
About me: I love walking around the neighborhood with my two wheatens, dancing, cooking, reading, watching movies, and teaching.

name: Artist's Cabin, peaceful, quiet, w/ Wi-Fi & trails
description: Your very own Private Cabin on Gated Property, next to wilderness, with hundreds of miles of fire roads, mountain bike and hiking trails in clean open air to refresh your spirit for a day trip or location. Skylights above a queen bed and a beautiful tile mosaic are just two of the many things that make this such a unique retreat.  Please ask, obvious questions are welcome
neighborhood_overview: We are off of a private road in a wilder part of Topanga. The neighbors are friendly but stay to themselves. Come armed with a smile is all you need. It is a short drive to Red Rock Canyon Park, or if you are fit you can hike 8 mile ridge loop that takes you around the canyon rim before it drops into Red Rock Canyon Park then back up to the cabin on Topanga Skyline Drive.
host_about:
I am a 30 year veteran of the Adventure Sports/Commercial Television and Film World.  I grew up between the Mountains of Colorado, in Vail and Aspen, and a large cattle ranch in Northwest Montana.  After a year of school at Prescott College in Arizona and several more shooting ski films in Colorado, I moved to North Hollywood where I lasted about 6 months before fleeing to Half Moon Bay.  I eventually made it back to Hollywood because of "The Business" and for about 5 years lived on my sailboat.  Throughout this time I was traveling the world shooting films and first kayak descents of rivers and ski descents of mountains.  About 10 years ago I met my sweetheart at the Premier of an IMAX Film called "Mystery of the Nile" we shot while making the first "Source to Sea" descent of the Nile.  After a couple of years living in the Marina we decided to settle in Topanga with our young family.  As luck would have it, we found a magical piece of property, with direct access to over 100 miles of hiking/mountain biking trails through Topanga State Park and adjacent wild areas, while being only 22 miles direct from downtown Los Angeles.  Now I am able to work closer to home and family.  Airbnb along with some beautiful property with stunning views is helping fulfill that dream....
As far as hosting, I would personally like to make everyone who stays with us a lifelong friend but I am also just happy to share a such a beautiful place so close to the city, yet so far away from all the noise and haste!  
If you decide to stay with us, you are welcome to request additional services like breakfast, cappuccino or a shuttle to the airport, direction and information on local resources.  We will do what we can to make sure our guests have a wonderful stay in a truly magical place with no worries about the small stuff.

name: Bungalow in the sky
description: Mid century furnishings. The house is 110 years old. Your living room is a huge deck with sweeping views of LA including Hollywood sign. Your own private entrance. Pretty cool spot. One in a million. Thanks
neighborhood_overview: Very cool and eclectic neighborhood. Many artists actors. Super groovy with fabulous walks to be had
host_about: Thank you for taking a look at my little tree house in the sky..My listing can be a bit confusing but here is the skinny. I usually am renting the downstairs unit which consists of a bedroom with a Queen size bed and walk in closet and very spacious bathroom with shower that has features for handicapped usage.. The living room is essentially a huge deck the size of a huge living room you can enjoy for yoga and working on outdoor furniture and chaise lounges.I also have my own private hiking trail behind my property and am very close to all the  cool eating and coffee shops Echo Park has to offer. I am 7 minutes to Echo Park lake and Silverlake reservoir which are both great for walking with your partner or pet if you bring either or both. I'm 3 minutes form Elysian Park which is attached to Dodger Stadium and is an incredible hiking and wildlife refuge. From the deck you have a spectacular view of the LA basin.You can see some of the most iconic sights of Los Angeles without leaving your bed.For example a beautiful view of Griffith Park ,Griffith Observatory, The Hollywood sign, Pacific Design Center,you can even see the Getty Center and Century City looking west. If you look the other direction you have all Glendale and Burbank and the snow covered mountains in winter. There is also quite a nice garden work in progress. You have your own private entrance and every amenity , cleaning and disinfecting products one would need. I tend to stock Kiehls and Aesop products. Also has nice small refrigerator and microwave.Flat screen TV wifi and every cable channel.  In other words I think you will love staying here.During these times,things have changed. I have never been one to have to give so many details. The place was always booked before the pandemic and I feel a need to reassure people that my place is safe and secure.With your own private entrance and (Website hidden by Airbnb) are free to use the kitchen upstairs which is a shared space or just shop for your own foods. There is no stove downstairs but their is a new microwave oven.Works great. Also hot watter kettle and coffee maker for your use.  I hope this helps somewhat in making your decisions to stay. Oh! and recently repainted and redid the whole deck!! There is also a fantastic grill outside for outdoor cooking. Ok I think Ive covered everything..Looking forward to seeing you soon.Best Ernesto ,Apple Jack and Isabella

name: ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚ñ†COLONEL'S 2BEDRM 1885 COTTAGE‚ñ†‚òÜ‚òÜ ~Old Town~
description: Welcome to the fully furnished 1,100 square foot 1885 private home of Colonel George Heath. This  pioneer drove a team of oxen from his home in Ohio to California in the 1852 gold rush and later migrated south to La Verne where he built his family home.  This 2 bedroom, 1 full bath home is located in the historic downtown area. It's high ceilings, wide baseboards & original pine floors are characteristic of the late 1800s while featuring central AC & heat, updated kitchen and newer bathroom.
neighborhood_overview:
The Colonel's Cottage is located in charming Old Town La Verne with many homes from the early 1900s and small eateries, all within walking distance. The Cottage is a block from the University of La Verne and walking distance to the Pomona Fairplex and Pomona Drag Way. Also a short drive to Raging Waters, Claremont McKenna University, Pitzer College, Scripps College, Harvey Mudd and downtown Claremont. It's about a 15 minute drive to Azusa Pacific University and Cal Poly Pomona.
Some great beaches about an hour away are Newport, Huntington and Laguna.

name: Penthouse Two @ World Artists Living
description:

Recently remodeled. Spared no expense with construction (if interested search World Artists Living for pics of next door props & grounds). We accept discounted corporate and local bookings on our site from guests needing housing for work, home renovation, etc. Please "contact host"!
neighborhood_overview:
World Artists Living is located at the corner of Las Palmas Avenue and Fountain Avenue. The area feels like a scene from a movie set.

The property is located in between two bustling boulevards ‚Äì Santa Monica Blvd and Sunset Blvd ‚Äì both walkable in 2-3 mins. My favorite feature about this location is having free parking straight outside, all while so much is walking distance. Even for any last minute odds and ends, the Las Palmas Market convenience store is located straight across the street along with our local fresh fruit stand.
host_about:
Hi, I‚Äôm Kevin.. I have properties in NYC and LA because of work in the music industry and this is still relatively early stages of my passion project. I got a couple of incredibly historic buildings across the street from my Hollywood house and converted the lot into stunning vacation homes. It started out with needing a guest house for friends who are touring musicians, actors and producers. Just search World Artists Living Hollywood if you‚Äôre interested in seeing more pictures and reviews. Our accommodations are designed to be like 'greenrooms from heaven'! Prior to working in music, I studied hotel management in college back home in Ireland. I began busking with friends in college days and one thing lead to another, so I had to shelve the tourism career for a while and hit the road touring.

I spent years living out of sleeper tour busses, airports, hotels, performing shows at huge venues, TV shows, etc. Days off in nice accommodations were a luxury for the band and crew. I definitely can relate to why former entertainment industry pros endorse and try to nail the perfect travel brand in retirement ;-)

You‚Äôre GUARANTEED NOT to find any silly $10 bottles of bedside water, broken appliances, and all that.. If you're looking for CLEAN, hassle free, place to call home for a few weeks - any of the World Artists Living properties are perfect! The majority of our guests now are traveling professionals. My aim is to provide 5 star hotel quality combined with the relaxed vibe of just being at your home (away from home). I work from my Hollywood house now and often invite guests over for drinks on my rooftop garden which is across the street from the rentals. Our housekeeper Natalia and her husband sometimes host grills on the rooftop for guests too. My parents ran a guesthouse when I was growing up in Ireland, long before AirBnB and their genuine hospitality is something that I aim to achieve with World Artists Living. Most guests have more interaction with Natalia than me as she's around the properties daily. We don't operate like a traditional hotel or run of the mill AirBnB - after check in you‚Äôll see that you‚Äôll be extremely comfortable and we run our properties like guest houses SHOULD BE RUN. 

If you‚Äôve stumbled across this searching Hollywood‚Äôs Suite, then that‚Äôs the unit across the street next to my home house. Guests staying at Hollywood‚Äôs Suite are welcome to use the GYM at World Artists Living complimentary. 

Thanks for reading if you got this far!

neighborhood_overview:
University Park is located just south of downtown Los Angeles and is primarily a residential neighborhood. It is home to the University of Southern California (USC), which is a major influence in the area.

The neighborhood has a mix of housing options, including single-family homes, apartment buildings, and student housing. Many students and faculty members of USC live in the area, giving it a vibrant and diverse atmosphere.

University Park is also known for its cultural and entertainment offerings. The area is close to the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, which has hosted major sporting events and concerts. The Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County and the California Science Center are also nearby, providing educational and recreational opportunities.

Overall, University Park is a lively and dynamic neighborhood with a strong academic presence and a range of amenities and attractions.

host_about:
Hello there! 

Thank you for visiting my host profile!
I was born and raised in the beautiful country of Morocco, from where I went to Paris to complete dental school. I finally settled in the sun-soaked City of Angels, where my husband lives. 

In the meantime, I gave up on being a dentist to pursue my passion for event planning. Now I coordinate high-end weddings and events while loving every minute of it. 

Hosting people is an activity I really enjoy, so turning our guesthouse into a short-vacation rental listing came like an easy choice. Through this endeavor, I aim to provide the best possible experience to all visitors through excellent service and quality local recommendations!. There is nothing more reassuring and calming than finding a place that feels like a second home on your travels.

Feel free to book or message me first; I am friendly, outgoing, and happy to answer any specific questions in advance.

I am a well-traveled guest who knows what a host should do to create a comfortable experience. My goal is to fulfill these requirements for every guest.

Experience Beverly Hills with me!  

Hope to host you soon!

This custom home featuring hand crafted original moldings and indoor balconies is a fabulous and unique place to stay for all kinds of visitors: from business professionals to large families to couples looking for a romantic getaway. neighborhood_overview:
Silver Lake is a hip and blossoming area. Home to many filmmakers, musicians and artists, Silver Lake is truly the place to be.

Within a short distance are a Vons, Gelsons and Trader Joe's supermarket. Yummy grocery store is but a 5-10 minute walk away and offers delivery of groceries. There's also the much beloved Saturday Silver Lake Farmer's Market. Also nearby Sunset Blvd and Silver Lake Blvd. host a large number of cafes and restaurants, such as the Black Cat Gastropub, Millie's Cafe, Subway, Cliff's Edge, El Pollo Loco, Lamill Coffee and Diablo Tacos. For those with a taste for night life try the Satellite night club, ACE's sport bar and grill, Los Globos latin music dance club or the Good Luck Bar and many more. Nearby Hollywood features many famous and well known clubs such as the Whiskey and The Roxy.
